  "text": "Formulation (5) suggests the use of Monte Carlo simulation based on stratified sampling. Each stratum k will be a set of all coalitions of the same size k. [CITATION_1] propose an heuristic method to allocate the samples into different strata. The approach provides a non-asymptotic bound for the sampling error by using Hoeffdings inequality (Hoeffding, 1963, Theorem 2.) to estimate the error within each stratum.",
